Kim Jong Il Provides Field Guidance to Mine 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 29 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il gave on-the-spot guidance to the March 5 Youth Mine. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He looked round the room devoted to the history of the mine. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He looked back with deep emotion on the glorious course of development covered by the mine which has advanced toward victory and prosperity under the care of President Kim Il Sung. Thanks to the wise guidance and meticulous care of the President, the mine has turned into a modern non-ferrous metal ore producer, he said, adding that his immortal revolutionary exploits will shine forever with the history of the mine. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then he was briefed on the ore body in front of its model picture and went round stopes to acquaint himself with the technical modernization of production processes and mineral output. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He dropped in at crushing and ore-dressing plants to learn in detail about the conditions of equipment and production and gave pep talks to workers speeding up the increased production for the prosperous development of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He said that the proud achievements made by the workers at the mine are a manifestation of the indomitable will of the Korean working class, the dependable ranks of loyal subjects who have overcome the stern trials of revolution victoriously, following the Party wholeheartedly. They are also a striking demonstration of the might of the most revolutionary and militant, heroic Korean workers who advance along the road of progress without slightest vacillation or hesitation in any adversity, he stressed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then he commanded a bird's-eye view of the mine reminiscent of a city. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He set forth tasks for systematically increasing the production at the mine and developing it under a long-term plan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The key to putting the non-ferrous metal production on a normal basis is to ensure the breaking and carriage of ore in a large quantity so as to keep concentrated ore production ahead of other works, he said, stressing the need to put in good order all the tunneling, carrying and dressing equipment and raise their operation rate. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In order to utilize the bountiful underground resources at the mine economically in a prospective way, he said it is necessary to give priority to the prospecting for providing enough ore reserves and thoroughly take steps for deep tunneling based on up-to-date science and technology. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On the same day he visited the Naedong Revolutionary Site in the seat of Jasong County. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The site is a historic place where Kim Hyong Jik, an indomitable revolutionary fighter, conducted his brisk activities for encouraging workers, peasants and other people of different strata in Jasong area to the anti-Japanese struggle in 1920 and autumn of 1921. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 After being briefed on the site in front of the monument to it, he looked round the historic buildings preserved as they were to acquaint himself with management of the site and education in it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He said that since there are many precious historic sites including the revolutionary sites associated with noble traces of the President, it is important to well preserve and manage them in their original state and intensify the education through them to more firmly arm party members and other working people, servicepersons and youth and children with the revolutionary idea of the WPK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He met with leading officials of the county to learn about the economic activities including farming and urged them to steadily increase the agricultural production so as to further improve the standard of living of the inhabitants in the county. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He was accompanied by Pak To Chun, chief secretary of the Jagang Provincial Committee of the WPK.

Message of Condolence to Indonesian President 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 29 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, Monday sent a message of condolence to Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono, President of Indonesia, on the death of Muhammad Soeharto, former President of Indonesia, from illness. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the message Kim expressed deep regret and consolation to the president and the family of the deceased.

Choe Thae Bok Meets Chinese Party Delegation 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 29 (KCNA) -- Choe Thae Bok, secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, met and had a friendly conversation with a delegation of the International Liaison Department of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China led by its Head Wang Jiarui on Tuesday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On hand were Kim Thae Jong, vice-director of a department of the WPK Central Committee, and Liu Xiaoming, Chinese ambassador to the DPRK.

Biochemical Warfare of U.S. Imperialism Is Inhuman Crime  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 29 (KCNA) -- The Korean people with surging indignation denounce the U.S. imperialists who perpetrated a biochemical warfare in the past Korean War. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@The aggressors dropped various kinds of germ bombs with cholera, typhoid, plague and other bacillus on 400-odd areas of the northern half of Korea on more than 700 occasions between Jan. 28 and Mar. 25, Juche 41 (1952) when the Korean War was in its thick. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@After that they massacred Koreans with toxic chemical weapons including poisonous gas bombs. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@It was an outrageous violation of the international law and an inhuman crime. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@In wanton violation of the international law on banning the use of germ and poisonous chemical weapons the U.S. imperialists have turned south Korea into a huge depot of biochemical weapons and are engaged in preparations for a biochemical warfare against the northern half of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@They shipped notorious defoliant into south Korea in the 1960s and have built 10-odd poisonous gas factories there to mass-produce various kinds of chemical weapons. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@They also brought dualistic chemical weapons, the weapon of devil, into over 40 bases of the U.S. army present in south Korea and moved their germ weapon-related units to south Korea from Japan. They established germ institutes in Korea University, Kyunghee University and so on for the purpose of research and production of germ weapons and their experiments. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@The United States has never missed the chemical warfare exercise when it held large-scale war exercises including Ulji Focus Lens in south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@It was reported that the chemical materials stockpiled in south Korea, Japan, Hawaii and other areas amount to 25,000 drums of 10-odd kinds. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@The army and people of the DPRK are closely watching the dangerous move of the U.S.    
