Anniversary of Kim Jong Il's Famous Work Observed  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 29 (KCNA) -- Papers here today dedicate signed articles to the 5th anniversary of the publication of Kim Jong Il's famous work "Songun-based Revolutionary Line Is a Great Revolutionary Line of Our Era and an Ever-Victorious Banner of Our Revolution ".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The work, published on Jan. 29, Juche 92 (2003), clarifies the essence and nature of the Songun revolutionary leadership and Songun policy of the Workers' Party of Korea and their revolutionary character and justice and inexhaustible vitality and the tasks to be fulfilled to advance the revolutionary cause of Juche at a new high level under the banner of Songun and ways to do so. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun says that the work serves as a monumental work of the times and an immortal militant banner for carrying out the Korean revolution and the cause of building a great prosperous powerful nation as it comprehensively deals with and elucidates the principle of the Songun revolution and the theory of the Songun policy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The past five years since the publication of the work are a proud history in which a great victory and change unprecedented in the Korean revolution and construction and national history have been brought about under the banner of Songun, the daily notes, and continues: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is a brilliant fruition of the Songun policy of the WPK that the military position of the Korean revolution has grown steel-strong and the single-minded unity of the revolutionary ranks has been consolidated in every way, a turning phase has been brought about for building a great prosperous powerful socialist nation and accomplishing the cause of national reunification and the international prestige of the country has risen higher than ever before. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the steadfast faith of the army and the people of the DPRK that the Korean revolution is sure to always triumph thanks to the Songun policy of the WPK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The reality today when all fields and units are pushing forward the revolution and construction on the principle of giving priority to the military affairs and by the Songun political mode and the traits of giving importance to arms and military affairs are prevailing throughout the society clearly indicates what tremendous vitality the ideas and theories expounded in the work display and how powerfully they encourage the people of the DPRK in the Songun revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Minju Joson calls on all officials and other working people to more deeply grasp those ideas and theories and thoroughly embody them in the on-going general offensive for building a great prosperous powerful nation and thus give fuller play to the validity and vitality of the Songun idea and Songun policy of the WPK.

U.S. Chiefly to Blame for Increasing Danger of Nuclear War in Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 29 (KCNA) -- South Korea still remains a powder keg of the U.S. for a dangerous nuclear war and this is a product of its adventurous strategy for world domination and the aggressive hostile policy towards the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun Tuesday says this in a signed article carried 50 years since the U.S. formally announced that it introduced nukes into south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Disclosing the criminal aim sought by the U.S. in having reduced south Korea to the most dangerous advance nuclear base in the world and brought the dark clouds of a nuclear war to hang over the Korean nation since the 1950s, the article goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. has long harbored the wild ambition to invade the DPRK with south Korea as a springboard and, furthermore, dominate the whole of Northeast Asia. The U.S. designated south Korea as a "vital operation area" as early as in the 1950s and has since stepped up the process of arming the U.S. forces in south Korea with nukes in real earnest. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. unilaterally declared the abrogation of the provision (d) of the Paragraph 13 of the Armistice Agreement banning the introduction of modern weapons at the 75th meeting of the Military Armistice Commission held in June 1957. And in July, it declared the start of the work to arm the U.S. forces in south Korea with nuclear weapons. On Jan. 29, 1958, the U.S. formally disclosed its introduction of nukes into south Korea. Few days later the U.S. opened to the public a 280mm atomic gun and nuclear missile "Honest John" at the command of the First Army Corps of the U.S. forces in south Korea and in May it test-fired the atomic gun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. policy for turning south Korea into a nuclear base has been steadily supplemented and perfected and put into a concrete shape in the subsequent period. Various types of nukes including nuclear bombs, nuclear mines and nuclear missiles produced in the U.S. were massively introduced into south Korea, pursuant to this policy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. had deployed more than 1,720 various tactical nuclear weapons in south Korea till the year before 1991, turning south Korea into the world's biggest nuclear base in the density of nuclear weapons deployment. Not content with this, the U.S. bellicose forces made the deployment of not only tactical nukes but also strategic nukes in south Korea an established fact, presupposing "contingency" on the Korean Peninsula at the 38th meeting of the south Korea-U.S. "annual security consultative council" held in October 2006. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 South Korea has thus turned into a huge powder keg for a dangerous nuclear war which may go off any moment and the situation on the peninsula remains so tense that a nuclear war may break out any moment due to the reckless moves of the U.S. which regards nukes as a means for carrying out its strategy for world domination and an all-powerful weapon for aggression and hegemony.

U.S. Responsible for Nuclear Issue in Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 29 (KCNA) -- The nuclear issue would not have surfaced on the Korean Peninsula if the U.S. had neither introduced nuclear weapons into south Korea nor threatened the DPRK with them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun Tuesday observes this in a signed commentary carried 50 years since the U.S. formally announced that it introduced nukes into south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that the U.S. introduction of nukes into south Korea was a very serious provocation to the DPRK as it amounted to challenging the just struggle of the Republic and all Koreans for peace and reunification of the country with a nuclear threat and it was a direct product of the U.S. aggressive strategy for world domination and its Korea policy, the commentary goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was the calculation of the U.S. to browbeat the DPRK and its neighboring countries with nukes in a bid to secure "upper-hand of strength" and carry out its adventurous policy for aggression with ease. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists have escalated their moves for a nuclear war against the DPRK for the last five decades, going against the desire of the Korean nation for peace. The U.S. has reduced south Korea to a huge powder keg for a nuclear war which may go off any moment and systematically increased the danger of a nuclear war on the Korean Peninsula, threatening the life and security of the Koreans and persistently standing in the way of their cause of peace and reunification. This is, indeed, a thrice-cursed crime. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The history and reality clearly prove that the U.S. is chiefly to blame for having escalated the danger of a nuclear war by spawning the nuclear issue on the peninsula and disturbing peace there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If the source of a nuclear war is to be removed from the peninsula, the U.S. should stop posing its nuclear threat to the DPRK and drop its hostile policy towards the latter and pull its forces for aggression out of south Korea, to begin with.

U.S. Projected Reorganization of Its Forces Assailed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 29 (KCNA) -- The United States is contemplating deploying "Global Hawk" and "F-22" in Guam and Hawaii military bases in the Pacific Ocean within this year, according to the "roadmap for the deployment of the U.S. air force in the 21st century" made public by the chief of staff of the U.S. air force sometime ago. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Commenting on this, Minju Joson Tuesday observes: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This indicates that the U.S. is regarding Asian-Pacific as the most important theatre of military activities of the U.S. forces in the 21st century and busy laying a foundation for implementing this scenario. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The news analyst goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the keynote of the U.S. defense strategy for the 21st century for its forces to carry out their reorganization in the direction of improving their maneuverability so that they may be rapidly hurled into any area for military actions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This fact reveals the ulterior motive of the above-said roadmap. It clearly hints that the think tanks of the U.S. military singled out Northeast Asia including the Korean Peninsula as a theatre of confrontation and an operational theatre for establishing their military hegemony. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 To stabilize the situation on the peninsula presents itself as a focus of world politics and a key issue at present.  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In this context the U.S. has an important and responsible part to play and once clarified its stand to seek a peaceful and negotiated settlement of the pending issues between the DPRK and the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This being a hard reality, U.S. negotiators say something before delegates of the DPRK but behave quite contrary to it after they are back. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The historical experience proves that the U.S. military pressure and hard-line policy has been of no help to developing the DPRK-U.S. relations but have driven the situation in this area into an extreme phase.  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 
 The U.S. would be well advised to cogitate about the serious consequences to be entailed by its anachronistic hostile policy towards the DPRK and take a right option.

Japanese Reactionaries' Anti-Chongryon Campaign Flailed
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 29 (KCNA) -- Recently, the Osaka District Court of Japan formally decided to dispose of the lands and building of the Osaka Korean Hall, where the Osaka prefectural headquarters of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon) is situated, to a real estate company. This is a grave political terrorism which can never be overlooked. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun Tuesday says this in a signed commentary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Now the Japanese reactionaries are disgustingly justifying such action as a mere "economic problem", the commentary notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Their decision to usurp the above-said building can never be a financial issue to be dealt with by any individual judicial body or company. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the ulterior intention of the Japanese reactionaries to destroy Chongryon by means of putting financial pressure upon it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 So, it is incontestable that the decision was made according to their deliberate scheme and direct instruction from beginning to the end. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 With any tricks they can never cover up their sinister intention to stamp out Chongryon and activities of Japan-resident Koreans by physically eliminating the strongholds of Chongryon. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries try to usurp the buildings and lands of Chongryon, not content with frantic suppression of it. Such actions fully reveal their brigandish nature, moral vulgarity and vileness. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Their moves are a direct outcome from Japan's hostile policy toward the DPRK. Particularly, lurking behind them is their criminal scheme to interrupt the process of the six-party talks and establish the domination over Asia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If Japan continues its moves to stifle Chongryon and seek a "cooperation mechanism for pressure" on the DPRK, the latter will be compelled to take a tougher counteraction.

Punishment on Ri Hoe Chang Urged in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 29 (KCNA) -- The South Headquarters of the National Alliance of Youth and Students for the Country's Reunification in south Korea reportedly made public a statement on Jan. 19 calling for all-out struggle to punish Ri Hoe Chang, a murderer. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Referring to the fact that Jo Yong Su, president of the newspaper "Minjok Ilbo" who was executed by the past military fascist clan, was given a verdict of not guilty on January 16, the statement disclosed that the judge who sentenced Jo to death in 1961 is none other than traitor Ri Hoe Chang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Branding Ri as a sycophantic traitor and a man-killer for having imposed death upon people desirous of independence, democracy and reunification, the statement said it is an intolerable insult to the people that such guy is allowed to swagger in south Korea, styling himself a politician.

Preparatory Committees Formed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 29 (KCNA) -- An Ukrainian national preparatory committee and a Kirgyz preparatory committee were formed with due ceremony on January 21 and 24 to commemorate the Day of the Sun and February 16. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Chairman of the Ukraine-DPRK Association Nikolai Polishk was elected chairman of the Ukrainian national preparatory committee and Chairman of the Marxist-Leninist Reunification Communist Party of the Kirgyzstan People A. Usupbayev chairman of the Kirgyz preparatory committee. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The preparatory committees decided to hold political and cultural events including meeting, lecture, seminar and film show and conduct activities for supporting the cause of the Korean people on the above-said occasions.

Bulletin Published in Italy to Mark Kim Jong Il's Birthday
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, January 29 (KCNA) -- The Italian Committee for the Study of Songun Idea for Independence and Sovereignty published its bulletin titled "Comrade Kim Jong Il Is a Great Politician and Great Philosopher" on Jan. 23 on the occasion of his birthday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The bulletin noted that though the imperialists have got evermore pronounced in the anti-socialist moves after the collapse of socialism in Eastern European countries in the late 20th century, the DPRK has been dynamically advancing along the road chosen by itself, holding higher the red flag without any slightest vacillation or hesitation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK is shining brilliantly as a country centered on the popular masses because Kim Jong Il saw to it that the Juche idea was thoroughly applied in the whole society, it pointed out. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Juche idea enriched by the leader is an original revolutionary doctrine based on the man-centered philosophical principle, the bulletin said, adding: This idea elucidates the profound truth that pride and honor of a nation lie in forming the harmonious whole of leader, party and masses of people and having its great leader.

Kim Yong Nam envia telegrama de condolencias al presidente indonesio
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 29 de enero (ATCC) -- El presidente del Presidium de la Asamblea Popular Suprema de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea, Kim Yong Nam, envio el dia 28 un telegrama de condolencias al presidente de la Republica de Indonesia, Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono, en relacion con el fallecimiento a causa de una enfermedad del ex presidente de este pais, Muhammad Suharto. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El remitente expresa sentidas condolencias y consuelo al destinatario y, por su conducto, a los familiares del difunto.

Rodong Sinmun estigmatiza a EE.UU. como fautor de problema nuclear
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 29 de enero (ATCC) -- Si Estados Unidos no hubiera introducido las armas nucleares en el Sur de Corea con las que amenaza al Norte de Corea, no habria surgido el problema nuclear en la Peninsula Coreana. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Asi senala el diario Rodong Sinmun en un comentario individual insertado en su numero del dia 29 con motivo de cumplirse 50 anos desde cuando EE.UU. dio a conocer oficialmente la introduccion de armas nucleares en el Sur de Corea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  El comentario va como sigue: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La introduccion de armas nucleares constituyo una grave provocacion respondiendo con la amenaza nuclear a la justa lucha de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea y la nacion coreana por la paz y la reunificacion del pais y al mismo tiempo fue producto evidente de la agresiva estrategia de hegemonia mundial y la politica de EE.UU. para con Corea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Ejerciendo la amenaza nuclear a la RPDC y los paises perifericos EE.UU. trato de ocupar la "supremacia de la fuerza" y realizar facilmente su aventurera politica de agresion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Durante estos 50 anos los imperialistas yanquis ampliaron de modo escalonado las maniobras de provocacion de guerra nuclear contra la RPDC nadando contra la aspiracion a la paz de la nacion coreana. EE.UU. convirtio al Sur de Corea en un peligroso polvorin de guerra nuclear, amenazo la vida y la seguridad de la nacion incrementando sistematicamente el peligro de guerra nuclear en la Peninsula Coreana e impidio siniestramente la causa de la paz y la reunificacion. Asi cometio un crimen nunca perdonable. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La historia y la realidad demuestran claramente que EE.UU. es precisamente el fautor que engendro el problema nuclear e incremento el peligro de guerra nuclear perturbando la paz en la Peninsula Coreana. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Para eliminar la fuente de la guerra nuclear en la Peninsula Coreana es preciso que EE.UU. renuncie su amenaza nuclear y la politica agresiva de hostilidad a la RPDC y retire sus tropas del Sur de Corea.
